Package model

Class IndexNumber

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.IndexNumber
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class IndexNumber
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is responsible for modelling the index number of a course which details the attributes and methods of each IndexNumber object for a particular Course object.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • registerNextStudentInWaitList

        public void registerNextStudentInWaitList()
                                   throws CourseRegisteredException,
                                          CourseInWaitListException,
                                          NoVacancyException,
                                          ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                          ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                                          MaxAuExceededException
        Removes the front most Student in the waitListStudents LinkedList of the IndexNumber and adds that Student into the registeredStudents ArrayList of the IndexNumber.
        Throws:
        CourseRegisteredException - if course is already registered.
        CourseInWaitListException - if course is already in wait list.
        NoVacancyException - if there are no more vacancies in the course.
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the index number to be registered clashes with any of the already registered index numbers
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - i.f the index number to be wait listed clashes with any of the already registered index numbers.
        MaxAuExceededException - if Student has reached the maximum amount of AUs.
        See Also:
        Student
